Armor, +1, +2, or +3
Armor (light, medium, or heavy), rare (+1), very rare (+2), or legendary (+3)

You have a bonus to AC while wearing this armor, the bonus is determined by its rarity.

When creating magical armor, consider using rare materials to describe these powerful armors. Of course, traditionally strong materials could be found in much lower quality. Use the following list as a guideline:

Light Armor
Rare (+1). Chitin, Mithril
Very Rare (+2). Elven
Legendary (+3). Dragonhide, Glass

Medium Armor
Rare (+1). Dreugh, Bonemold
Very Rare (+2). Stahlrim, Orcish
Legendary (+3). Dragonscale

Heavy Armor
Rare (+1). Dwemer, Adamantium
Very Rare (+2). Ebony
Legendary (+3). Daedric, Dragonplate


Weapon, +1, +2, or +3
Weapon (any), uncommon (+1), rare (+2), or rare (+3)

You have a bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. The bonus is determined by the weapon's rarity.

When creating magical weapons, consider using rare materials to describe these powerful weapons. Of course, traditionally strong materials could be found in much lower quality. Use the following list as a guideline:

Magic Weapons
Uncommon (+1). Elven, Mithril, Dwarven
Rare (+2). Orcish, Adamantium, Ebony
Very Rare (+3). Daedric, Dragonbone

